1
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:40,440
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:41,870
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:45,110 --> 00:00:47,080
(Episode 6)

4
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:56,620
What a pair...

5
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:08,600
What's this for?

6
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,400
Are you making flower pancakes?

7
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,470
Did Director Shin ask for them?

8
00:01:13,340 --> 00:01:14,510
Or are you just making them?

9
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:22,550
Are you all ignoring me?
Is Director Shin your only deity now?

10
00:01:25,890 --> 00:01:28,190
You too? Hey, Lee Shim!

11
00:01:30,190 --> 00:01:31,190
Park Soo!

12
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:36,760
I can fire you both.

13
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:48,240
I'll be the one making
Director Shin's birthday dinner this time.

14
00:01:52,650 --> 00:01:54,280
Don't you two work well together...

15
00:01:54,980 --> 00:01:55,980
Why not just get married?

16
00:01:57,180 --> 00:01:58,180
Who's the senior here?

17
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:00,520
Lee Shim.

18
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:03,190
How old are you?

19
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:06,790
It's impossible to tell her age.

20
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,700
You all have no manners.

21
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,880
I looked into it,
and on that day, two babies...

22
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:27,650
Yes...

23
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,320
But...

24
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:39,990
I don't think it's you.

25
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:42,230
I just have a feeling.

26
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:44,660
You don't resemble my family at all.

27
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:49,270
Family members don't always
have to look alike.

28
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:53,540
What about the other child
left at the church that day?

29
00:02:54,110 --> 00:02:55,740
- Yes.
- Can you get in touch with her?

30
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:58,480
Yes.

31
00:02:59,610 --> 00:03:03,350
Could you explain the situation
and arrange for me to meet them?

32
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:07,020
Yes, but shouldn't we get a test done?

33
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,920
I'll meet her first.

34
00:03:09,420 --> 00:03:11,220
If I feel she isn't the one either...

35
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,530
What's her name?

36
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,130
Kim Jin Ju.

37
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:21,870
We even have the same last name.

38
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,710
I'd like to call her now.

39
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:29,510
I'll try calling her.

40
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,780
(Kim Jin Ju)

41
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,720
The phone is turned off.

42
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:39,650
Please leave a message after the tone.

43
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,790
She must be working.

44
00:03:41,450 --> 00:03:42,460
Her phone's off.

45
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:47,390
- What does she do?
- Jin Ju?

46
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:49,530
- Yes.
- She's a stylist.

47
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:53,770
- Like celebrity outfits?
- Yes.

48
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,100
And where did she go to school?

49
00:03:58,570 --> 00:04:01,240
You can ask her that in person.

50
00:04:12,450 --> 00:04:14,920
You seem to have a job too.

51
00:04:15,190 --> 00:04:16,290
Yes.

52
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,130
- Where do you work?
- The culture desk at Sungwoo Daily.

53
00:04:20,990 --> 00:04:21,990
You're a reporter?

54
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:24,830
Yes. And you?

55
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,200
I was away...

56
00:04:27,330 --> 00:04:29,040
this year for a while.

57
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:33,210
When Kim Jin Ju gets in touch,
could you give her my number?

58
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:36,240
Okay. But...

59
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:39,910
you really don't think it's me?

60
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,650
Do you want me to be your dad?

61
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:49,790
I need to meet everyone to know for sure.

62
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:01,670
They're treating him
like he's absolute royalty.

63
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:06,970
I don't eat carbs.

64
00:05:19,150 --> 00:05:20,490
Did you say you wanted to eat these?

65
00:05:22,090 --> 00:05:24,290
It's because I remember how my mom
used to make them for me...

66
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:25,860
around this time of year.

67
00:05:27,990 --> 00:05:31,100
So your comfort food is azalea pancakes?

68
00:05:32,330 --> 00:05:33,370
For me,

69
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,870
it's chive and pumpkin pancakes.

70
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,270
I hate the word "bindaetteok."

71
00:05:39,770 --> 00:05:42,440
It just sounds so destitute and poor.

72
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,680
I'll make your birthday dinner this time.

73
00:05:45,810 --> 00:05:47,950
Something really special and grand.

74
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:49,550
We'll invite your friends.

75
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:50,880
I'm busy.

76
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,290
And it's too much trouble.

77
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:55,020
Still, you should have
at least one proper meal.

78
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:58,160
Shouldn't you be resting in bed?

79
00:05:58,660 --> 00:05:59,660
I'm much better now.

80
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:01,530
I've pulled a muscle before.

81
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:03,100
Right.

82
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,760
It wasn't this body.

83
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:08,800
What dishes do you miss the most
made by your mother?

84
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:10,970
Meat and rice.

85
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:13,610
Meat and rice? How do you make it?

86
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:16,580
Even when Nurse Park uses prime beef,
it just doesn't taste the same.

87
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:17,910
Although it might look the same.

88
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:21,110
When will you stop being so formal?

89
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:22,620
It's going to become a habit.

90
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,480
What if someone hears you?

91
00:06:27,290 --> 00:06:28,290
I'll get there.

92
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:31,290
I know men can't keep secrets.

93
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:33,060
Are you telling Ha Yong Joong everything?

94
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:37,200
It's always the ones closest to you
who betray you.

95
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,700
Hey.

96
00:06:40,970 --> 00:06:43,340
You called? I'm out working.

97
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:45,400
This time,

98
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:49,240
you might actually get to meet
your biological dad.

99
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:50,940
Is someone looking for me again?

100
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:53,410
The Self-Reliance Center director
contacted me.

101
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:56,450
So, I met a man named Kim Gwang Cheol.

102
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:57,680
Kim Jin Ju!

103
00:06:58,580 --> 00:06:59,790
You're not done yet?

104
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:01,350
I have two scenes left.

105
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:03,120
I'm the last one off,

106
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,360
so I don't think I'll be done
until after 1 a.m.

107
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:07,890
The news stories drop at dawn,
so I need to get to sleep now.

108
00:07:08,530 --> 00:07:10,160
- Tomorrow, then?
- Okay.

109
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,520
James!

110
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,390
Hey, you're here.

111
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:41,060
What is all this?

112
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:43,200
A monk I know...

113
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:44,960
What about a monk?
Did he give this to you?

114
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:47,000
- Yes.
- Why?

115
00:07:47,730 --> 00:07:48,800
Are you hungry?

116
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:50,640
Let's have breakfast. It's been a while.

117
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,300
It'll just take 30 minutes.

118
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:06,050
Why did he tell you to do this?

119
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:08,590
I told him I had insomnia.

120
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:10,220
Does it work? Are you sleeping?

121
00:08:10,790 --> 00:08:11,790
Yes.

122
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:13,390
So is this the logic?

123
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:16,160
When you get sleep paralysis,
the spirits see this and can't get you?

124
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,400
Want rice or toast?

125
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:32,380
So you gave the painting
to Ba Ra after all.

126
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:34,780
No.

127
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,850
"Do you want to take it back
and continue our relationship?"

128
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:42,690
"Or should I take the artwork,
and we go our separate ways?"

129
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:45,060
When she puts it like that, what can I do?
I had to take it back.

130
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:48,090
She even rejects you in a lovely way,
making you feel good about it.

131
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:49,500
Don't take it too far.

132
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:50,900
Even if I don't,

133
00:08:51,330 --> 00:08:52,730
you know what they say,

134
00:08:52,730 --> 00:08:54,470
"You can't hide love, poverty,
or a cough."

135
00:08:54,730 --> 00:08:55,840
Hide it.

136
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,470
If you cause trouble by being selfish,

137
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,910
I'll be really disappointed in you.

138
00:09:05,010 --> 00:09:06,610
I'm saying this because it's us.

139
00:09:06,610 --> 00:09:09,450
I don't think of Professor Lee
or Professor Shin as someone I'd marry.

140
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:11,420
It's just for a bit of fun,
a passing interest.

141
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:16,160
Reporter Geum may be smart
and have the looks and pedigree,

142
00:09:16,420 --> 00:09:18,790
but would just any family accept her
as a daughter-in-law?

143
00:09:22,260 --> 00:09:25,730
The age gap aside, she's perfect for me.

144
00:09:25,730 --> 00:09:26,900
We're kindred spirits.

145
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,670
Age doesn't matter these days,
as long as you don't look old.

146
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:32,000
You think you can control that?

147
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:35,470
We have the world's best cosmetic tech.

148
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:36,780
It's too late for you.

149
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,240
They'll say you're going senile.

150
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:40,410
Don't you know what people look for
in a marriage prospect?

151
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,410
I don't. All I know is love.

152
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,180
So you think it's best just to rip
the band-aid off?

153
00:09:44,180 --> 00:09:45,990
Then go on and confess everything to her.

154
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:48,890
You'll probably never see her again.

155
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,420
Want to bet?

156
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:54,790
He said he doesn't think it's me.
I don't look alike at all.

157
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:56,760
What does he look like?
His clothes and everything.

158
00:09:57,860 --> 00:09:59,670
- He's just average.
- You mean shabby?

159
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:01,270
No.

160
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:03,670
But we were the only two babies left...

161
00:10:03,940 --> 00:10:05,940
at that church on December 21, 1999.

162
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:08,540
You have the same last name as him,
so it has to be you.

163
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:10,740
I'm so nervous.

164
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,510
I'll text you his number.

165
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,670
Kim Jin Ju?

166
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:16,940
Yes.

167
00:11:30,660 --> 00:11:32,160
An iced Americano, please.

168
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,190
- Same for me.
- Okay.

169
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:37,330
We don't even need a DNA test.

170
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:41,470
You're the spitting image of the mother
you've never even met.

171
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,200
Really?

172
00:11:45,070 --> 00:11:46,140
Do you have a picture?

173
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,040
You don't?

174
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:52,210
I don't have one.

175
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,610
We weren't married.

176
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,080
What was your relationship, exactly?

177
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:59,450
So you just dated and then broke up?

178
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:02,250
Or were you already married
when you met her,

179
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:05,420
- and I was the result of an affair?
- No.

180
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:07,530
We dated for about a year.

181
00:12:07,730 --> 00:12:10,600
When we drifted apart,
I didn't even know she was pregnant.

182
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:13,600
How...

183
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,940
I didn't know...

184
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:20,310
Her name was Hwang Mi Sook.

185
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:23,980
- My birth mother?
- Yes.

186
00:12:24,580 --> 00:12:27,180
She left you with my mother
and then disappeared.

187
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:30,050
- So...
- Then who threw me away...

188
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:31,650
in the box at Minjin Church?

189
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:35,990
- I wouldn't say threw away...
- But that's what it was.

190
00:12:38,460 --> 00:12:40,230
I only found out later.

191
00:12:40,730 --> 00:12:41,890
Then my grandmother did it?

192
00:12:42,660 --> 00:12:45,730
Let's not speak ill of the dead.

193
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,430
Her own flesh-and-blood granddaughter?

194
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,040
Given her circumstances,

195
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,070
how could an old woman raise you all
on her own?

196
00:12:53,070 --> 00:12:54,610
Then what were you doing?

197
00:12:56,140 --> 00:12:58,540
Do people only raise kids and grandkids
when things are easy?

198
00:12:59,180 --> 00:13:00,810
That was a long time ago.

199
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:04,750
- Does the past really matter?
- "The past doesn't matter?"

200
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:07,690
I grew up in an orphanage
without any parents.

201
00:13:12,290 --> 00:13:13,630
I'm so ashamed.

202
00:13:14,490 --> 00:13:16,600
You must resent me so much.
I would too, in your shoes.

203
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:18,960
Look, it's a long story.

204
00:13:20,270 --> 00:13:22,840
I heard you studied fashion design.

205
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,540
At Seshin Community College.

206
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,510
I'm so proud. You've turned out so well.

207
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:30,640
Are you really sure about this?

208
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,610
Of course. I recognized you right away.

209
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:35,150
You're the spitting image of your mom
in her twenties.

210
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:38,320
You look a bit like your grandmother, too.
I have a picture of her.

211
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:39,380
I don't want to see it.

212
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:47,690
From your grandmother's point of view,
she'd only heard one side of the story,

213
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:51,760
and she doubted if you were really
her son's flesh and blood.

214
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:55,270
Plus, she had a bad leg. So...

215
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:57,870
If she cared so much,
did she at least write my name on a note?

216
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:00,340
No.

217
00:14:00,610 --> 00:14:04,240
Anyway, she told me the exact date
and everything.

218
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:07,210
She made me promise to find you
and make sure.

219
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,520
And you're just now getting to it?

220
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,480
Here are your coffees.

221
00:14:17,620 --> 00:14:19,560
Did something happen
that you can't talk about?

222
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:22,630
No, there's nothing I can't talk about.

223
00:14:23,660 --> 00:14:25,200
Let's get something to eat first.

224
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:27,370
People get cranky when they're hungry.

225
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:31,100
- Didn't you have breakfast?
- Isn't it lunchtime?

226
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:32,910
Do you often skip meals?

227
00:14:33,410 --> 00:14:35,840
Don't do that. It's bad for your health.

228
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:39,610
I saw a restaurant in the lobby
on my way in.

229
00:14:40,710 --> 00:14:42,080
They might not have a table.

230
00:14:42,550 --> 00:14:44,320
If they don't,
we can just eat somewhere else.

231
00:14:51,220 --> 00:14:52,320
Hello.

232
00:14:53,290 --> 00:14:54,330
Thank you.

233
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:02,600
Where do you live?

234
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:04,540
In a studio.

235
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,970
No, I mean, which neighborhood?

236
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,070
Hyeonmi-dong.

237
00:15:10,610 --> 00:15:11,880
And you work around here?

238
00:15:13,010 --> 00:15:14,050
In Gangnam.

239
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:18,920
Do you have a reservation?

240
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:21,150
- No.
- A table for two?

241
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:23,890
- Yes.
- Let me check for a table.

242
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:27,260
Do you have a business card?

243
00:15:34,830 --> 00:15:36,700
(Kim Jin Ju, Staff, Lim Company)

244
00:15:39,570 --> 00:15:40,740
Where do you live?

245
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:42,110
What?

246
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:45,040
I need to find a place now.

247
00:15:45,810 --> 00:15:47,150
Did you live abroad?

248
00:15:47,450 --> 00:15:49,050
Right this way.

249
00:15:49,510 --> 00:15:50,520
Okay.

250
00:15:56,990 --> 00:15:59,120
I'm afraid all the private rooms
are taken.

251
00:16:04,430 --> 00:16:06,700
Hello? Oh, hello, sir.

252
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:32,390
Tomorrow? Alright. Thank you.

253
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:49,810
(Kim Jin Ju, December 3, 1999)

254
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:59,120
(Kim Jin Ju, December 3, 1999)

255
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:08,490
Look at CEO Ju, schmoozing.

256
00:17:14,730 --> 00:17:16,640
(Art Folder...)

257
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:18,440
(Culture Desk 3)

258
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:19,810
Do you have plans tonight?

259
00:17:20,870 --> 00:17:22,240
- No.
- That's good.

260
00:17:22,510 --> 00:17:24,410
I'm meeting CEO Ju Yeong Ae. Join me.

261
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:26,110
Is it okay if I come?

262
00:17:26,110 --> 00:17:27,780
You covered her last exhibition,
didn't you?

263
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:30,280
- But you were the one who...
- French food at the Sun Hotel.

264
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:38,260
Order whatever you want.

265
00:17:40,190 --> 00:17:42,360
- You have the lunch special, right?
- Yes.

266
00:17:42,430 --> 00:17:44,300
- We'll have that.
- The lunch special for two?

267
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,360
Yes.

268
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,370
Isn't a studio apartment
a little dangerous...

269
00:17:50,740 --> 00:17:51,840
for a woman on her own?

270
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:53,310
It's fine.

271
00:17:54,410 --> 00:17:55,470
What about a boyfriend?

272
00:17:57,010 --> 00:17:58,010
I don't have one.

273
00:18:00,450 --> 00:18:01,710
I'm a man myself,

274
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:04,220
but there's really no need
to get married these days.

275
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:07,520
If you do, do it later in life,
after you've done everything you want.

276
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:13,330
I've learned that life doesn't
always go as planned.

277
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:18,400
I don't know what you'll think of me
for saying this,

278
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:22,830
but as time went on, I missed you
more and more, and I wondered...

279
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:26,810
if you'd be tall or short,
or if you took after me at all.

280
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:31,540
You never left my mind or my heart.

281
00:18:33,650 --> 00:18:36,380
Hwang Mi Sook wouldn't lie
about our child,

282
00:18:36,380 --> 00:18:37,850
and she has no reason to.

283
00:18:38,950 --> 00:18:41,590
For 27 years,
I failed to be a father to you,

284
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:45,390
so I'll do my best to make up for it
and then some from now on.

285
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,830
Are you managing to save
any of the money you earn?

286
00:19:01,170 --> 00:19:02,710
Let's eat before it gets cold.

287
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:15,820
This is delicious.

288
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:21,630
She kept appearing in my dreams
for a while,

289
00:19:22,260 --> 00:19:24,100
and now it's like she's been
reincarnated or something.

290
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:27,730
Have you ever told her you love her?

291
00:19:28,370 --> 00:19:29,400
To Oiji?

292
00:19:31,070 --> 00:19:32,070
Did I?

293
00:19:33,670 --> 00:19:35,440
Of course I loved her.

294
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:39,810
You know, Ba Ra likes puppies too.

295
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:44,680
I wonder if she'd accept
a puppy as a gift.

296
00:19:45,020 --> 00:19:46,990
Ms. Noh Hye Yeong said she was
running 30 minutes late.

297
00:19:47,190 --> 00:19:49,760
That woman has no sense of time.

298
00:19:51,060 --> 00:19:52,360
Is Jin Ju out on set?

299
00:19:52,690 --> 00:19:53,790
It's her day off today.

300
00:19:58,700 --> 00:19:59,700
It's uncanny.

301
00:20:00,330 --> 00:20:02,170
It's like I'm sitting here
with Hwang Mi Sook.

302
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:05,900
What did she do for a living?

303
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,410
A nurse.

304
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:10,980
At what hospital?

305
00:20:12,810 --> 00:20:15,880
I found out she got married and emigrated.

306
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,590
If you're anything like me,

307
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:27,830
you're probably a very honest person.

308
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:30,360
I don't hide things or deceive people.

309
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:35,370
You'll find out eventually anyway.
I was away at "school" all this time.

310
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,040
You know what I mean by "school," right?

311
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:39,300
Prison.

312
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:44,510
That's why I couldn't look for you,
even though I desperately wanted to.

313
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:48,380
I got tangled up in some things,
and parts of it were unfair,

314
00:20:50,220 --> 00:20:51,780
but I just see it all as fate.

315
00:20:54,220 --> 00:20:56,090
For that long?

316
00:20:56,490 --> 00:20:58,590
I got out on parole eight years ago.

317
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:02,560
But you went back in?

318
00:21:02,990 --> 00:21:07,600
From now on, I'm going to live for you,
and only for you.

319
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:10,340
That's why I came looking for you
with so much confidence.

320
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,070
Are you disappointed?

321
00:21:16,410 --> 00:21:18,010
Were you hoping for some big-shot parents?

322
00:21:19,740 --> 00:21:23,280
The past is in the past.
You have to live for the future.

323
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:25,980
There's no moving forward
if you're stuck in the past.

324
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:28,420
You're not alone in the world anymore.

325
00:21:28,790 --> 00:21:31,720
You have a dad you can count on,
so hold your head high.

326
00:21:32,990 --> 00:21:37,260
If you have even the slightest doubt,
we can get a test tomorrow to be sure.

327
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,130
No.

328
00:21:41,130 --> 00:21:44,740
There were only two babies left there
on December 21, 1999.

329
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,910
Geum Ba Ra doesn't look anything like me.

330
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:49,410
You just know
when it's your own flesh and blood.

331
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:53,410
Is there anything you're curious about,

332
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:54,880
or anything you wish for?

333
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,120
I'll have to think about it.

334
00:22:00,990 --> 00:22:02,120
Why aren't you eating?

335
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:05,660
- I'm full.
- Are you on a diet?

336
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:07,960
I just don't have much of an appetite.

337
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:21,670
So, family shouldn't live apart, right?

338
00:22:21,970 --> 00:22:23,580
We need to save money on rent.

339
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:27,050
I don't have much stuff anyway.
I could move in tomorrow.

340
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:30,080
- To my place?
- Yes.

341
00:22:30,650 --> 00:22:32,450
- Why?
- What do you mean, "why?"

342
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:33,890
Aren't we family?

343
00:22:35,390 --> 00:22:37,560
It's a studio apartment. Just one room.

344
00:22:38,460 --> 00:22:39,760
I know it's a studio.

345
00:22:40,230 --> 00:22:41,760
It has a living room and kitchen area,
doesn't it?

346
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:45,030
I can just sleep in a corner.
I just need a sleeping bag.

347
00:22:54,710 --> 00:22:56,740
- Hello.
- Hello.

348
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:02,550
What about Kim Jeong Ah?

349
00:23:02,610 --> 00:23:04,250
She had to kill a story
at the last minute.

350
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:05,280
I see.

351
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:07,120
A journalist I’m close with once said,

352
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:10,990
"Being a reporter would be a great job
if you didn't have to write stories."

353
00:23:11,620 --> 00:23:12,620
That's what she said.

354
00:23:13,090 --> 00:23:14,090
Right.

355
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:23,900
Hello.

356
00:23:25,770 --> 00:23:26,770
A pleasure to meet you.

357
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:33,080
Our reporter, Kim Jeong Ah,
had to kill a story at the last minute.

358
00:23:33,510 --> 00:23:35,980
- So I'm here instead.
- Well, not "instead."

359
00:23:36,650 --> 00:23:38,350
Your exhibition article was so great,

360
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:41,190
I've been meaning to set something up.

361
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,090
There was so much great work
to write about.

362
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:45,260
How long did it take to prepare?

363
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:46,660
Almost a year.

364
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:51,900
Ma'am, the hospital just called.
She's suddenly taken a turn for the worse.

365
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:57,670
My mother-in-law is in the ICU.

366
00:23:58,140 --> 00:24:00,940
- You should go right away.
- I'm so sorry about this.

367
00:24:01,070 --> 00:24:02,110
Which hospital?

368
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:07,810
- Korea Sam Hospital.
- But traffic is terrible right now.

369
00:24:08,050 --> 00:24:10,880
- I'll take care of the bill later...
- No, please don't worry about it.

370
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:13,150
- Go on.
- No, really.

371
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:16,920
Well, I'll make it up to you next time.
Please, don't get up.

372
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:18,260
You too.

373
00:24:26,430 --> 00:24:29,070
Oh, Father

374
00:24:31,270 --> 00:24:34,070
Oh, Father

375
00:24:36,470 --> 00:24:41,250
Our prayers

376
00:24:43,010 --> 00:24:45,720
Please, answer them

377
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:52,690
Answer them?

378
00:24:52,690 --> 00:24:54,330
(Answer them?)

379
00:24:54,490 --> 00:24:55,490
My foot.

380
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:58,330
(My foot.)

381
00:25:03,330 --> 00:25:06,100
I've never met an artist based in Germany.

382
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:07,670
How did you end up there?

383
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:08,970
This isn't an interview, by the way.

384
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:12,080
My closest friend
from my high school class...

385
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:13,710
went to study abroad in Germany.

386
00:25:14,010 --> 00:25:15,450
So you followed your friend to Germany?

387
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:17,080
You could say that.

388
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:20,450
When you live there a long time,
do you start to become like the locals?

389
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:24,660
Do I seem a bit stiff?
I get that sometimes.

390
00:25:25,020 --> 00:25:29,730
You definitely have a different vibe
from most Korean men your age.

391
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:33,130
I'm a Korean man too.

392
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:36,270
I just had to change my citizenship,
that's all.

393
00:25:37,570 --> 00:25:39,970
You're not much of a talker, are you?

394
00:25:40,100 --> 00:25:42,710
This is our second time meeting,
and that's the sense I'm getting.

395
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:44,710
I'll make an exception today.

396
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:49,480
How do you feel about
the positive reaction...

397
00:25:49,910 --> 00:25:51,050
your work has been getting in Korea?

398
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:54,920
Sorry. That came out sounding
like an interview question.

399
00:25:54,990 --> 00:25:57,860
When my hard work is seen and appreciated,

400
00:25:58,120 --> 00:25:59,190
it feels good, of course.

401
00:26:00,090 --> 00:26:01,990
I think people are drawn to the affection
in my work.

402
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:04,800
Is that the main theme?

403
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,000
Isn't it?

404
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:11,670
How many years were you in Germany?
It seems like it's been over 20.

405
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,210
Yes, a full 26 years.

406
00:26:14,570 --> 00:26:16,370
But your Korean is perfect.

407
00:26:16,670 --> 00:26:19,610
- Is your best friend still there...
- No.

408
00:26:19,910 --> 00:26:21,480
I never even got to meet him there.

409
00:26:22,610 --> 00:26:24,650
I was in an accident
the day after I arrived.

410
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:27,220
My gosh, what kind of accident?

411
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:28,550
A car accident.

412
00:26:29,620 --> 00:26:32,890
I had a pretty bad head injury,
so I was unconscious for a while.

413
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:35,090
And even after I woke up,
I was in and out of it for a few years.

414
00:26:35,490 --> 00:26:38,000
- Oh, dear.
- So I never had the chance to find him.

415
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:41,730
I actually met up with him
when I came back to Korea this time.

416
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,140
Turns out he's a managing director
at Jeil Auto.

417
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:45,670
You must have been so happy to see him.

418
00:26:46,370 --> 00:26:47,370
Yes.

419
00:26:47,370 --> 00:26:49,770
After almost three decades,

420
00:26:50,170 --> 00:26:51,780
Korea's changed a lot, hasn't it?

421
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:55,510
- Yes.
- How many times did you return?

422
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:58,020
Just once, 11 years ago...

423
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:01,490
It was when my mother passed away.

424
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:04,460
I couldn't be there when my father passed.

425
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:07,690
You must have gone through a lot
in Germany.

426
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,930
But it turned out to be
a lucky break, in a way.

427
00:27:10,500 --> 00:27:12,560
The person who caused my accident
passed away last year.

428
00:27:13,430 --> 00:27:14,530
He was my adoptive father.

429
00:27:14,870 --> 00:27:17,770
- Oh my.
- He must have felt so guilty about it,

430
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:22,210
though he always said it was
because he recognized my talent.

431
00:27:22,610 --> 00:27:23,880
He adopted me as his son.

432
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:28,580
Thanks to him,
my language skills improved quickly,

433
00:27:29,110 --> 00:27:32,420
and he was a famous painter and professor,
Ilias Becker.

434
00:27:32,950 --> 00:27:34,150
You can look him up.

435
00:27:34,690 --> 00:27:36,590
He truly saved my life.

436
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,760
So that's how you got your citizenship.

437
00:27:40,020 --> 00:27:42,690
I just assumed
you had married a German woman.

438
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:45,230
A blessing in disguise, isn't it?

439
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:47,600
To think that an unfortunate accident
led to...

440
00:27:47,730 --> 00:27:50,800
Yes. You win some, and you lose some.

441
00:27:50,970 --> 00:27:53,040
And misfortune can turn into good luck.

442
00:27:53,100 --> 00:27:55,510
You must believe that
someone up there was looking out for you.

443
00:27:55,670 --> 00:27:58,380
I believe that the skies help
those who help themselves.

444
00:27:59,140 --> 00:28:03,620
As my father's assistant and secretary,
studying and working on my art,

445
00:28:04,780 --> 00:28:07,590
I don't think
I had a single second to spare.

446
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:09,320
That's incredible.

447
00:28:10,250 --> 00:28:12,920
Are you okay now, health-wise?
Are there any lingering effects?

448
00:28:13,020 --> 00:28:14,130
I recovered fully.

449
00:28:14,390 --> 00:28:16,430
I even slept less
to make time to exercise.

450
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:21,370
Listening to you makes me realize
how much further I have to go.

451
00:28:21,730 --> 00:28:24,500
You made it as a reporter
for Sungwoo Daily by giving it your all.

452
00:28:25,300 --> 00:28:26,500
They don't just hand you that job,
do they?

453
00:28:28,310 --> 00:28:31,510
- Mr. Kim. I mean, sir.
- Call me what you're comfortable with.

454
00:28:34,250 --> 00:28:35,810
Thinking about Korea now
versus when you left,

455
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:39,120
is there anything that's changed
in a way you don't like?

456
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:41,590
When do you feel out of place?

457
00:28:42,820 --> 00:28:44,120
I'm asking a lot of questions, aren't I?

458
00:28:44,460 --> 00:28:45,690
There's just so much I'm curious about.

459
00:28:46,020 --> 00:28:47,290
No, this is what
we're supposed to talk about.

460
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:49,890
Otherwise,
we'd just be staring at each other.

461
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:52,960
One thing that throws me off sometimes...

462
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:55,770
Maybe it's because I'm used to
the German way of thinking,

463
00:28:56,370 --> 00:28:59,770
but it's when people just hit you
with personal questions out of nowhere.

464
00:29:01,210 --> 00:29:04,210
Like, "Why aren't you married?"
or "Have you ever dated a German woman?"

465
00:29:04,310 --> 00:29:05,840
Or, "Let me set you up with someone."

466
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:06,910
Yes.

467
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:09,280
That's just our way of showing we care.

468
00:29:10,010 --> 00:29:13,750
But we should focus that energy
on ourselves.

469
00:29:14,150 --> 00:29:15,190
Excuse me.

470
00:29:15,390 --> 00:29:17,590
Of all the photos taken of me in Korea,

471
00:29:18,590 --> 00:29:19,760
this is my favorite.

472
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:31,700
(Yong Joong)

473
00:29:36,470 --> 00:29:37,580
It's been a while.

474
00:29:37,910 --> 00:29:39,080
Do I always have to call first?

475
00:29:39,540 --> 00:29:41,410
I could tell you were busy.

476
00:29:42,110 --> 00:29:45,080
Did you bug my place?
You've never even been to my house.

477
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:47,190
I just close my eyes,
and I can see everything.

478
00:29:47,590 --> 00:29:50,190
Seeing whoever I thought about
would be a great power.

479
00:29:52,620 --> 00:29:53,690
Momo?

480
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:55,660
No, you.

481
00:29:58,530 --> 00:29:59,560
You're home, right?

482
00:29:59,900 --> 00:30:00,900
Yes.

483
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:05,340
Come to think of it,
you've never invited me over.

484
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:07,970
That's why I'm calling.
I want to invite you over today.

485
00:30:09,740 --> 00:30:12,410
- How long will that take?
- You're here?

486
00:30:12,580 --> 00:30:14,710
- Yes.
- Oh my gosh.

487
00:30:14,780 --> 00:30:17,050
Don't worry about dressing up.
Just come as you are.

488
00:30:17,750 --> 00:30:18,750
One minute.

489
00:30:38,340 --> 00:30:40,040
When did you get so pretty?

490
00:30:40,510 --> 00:30:41,740
I've always been pretty.

491
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,650
- Are we really going to your place?
- Yes.

492
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:56,720
Then I should get you something.
It's my first visit.

493
00:30:57,190 --> 00:30:58,860
- Did you have lunch?
- Of course.

494
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:01,430
- You haven't yet?
- It's not that I didn't eat, I couldn't.

495
00:31:01,430 --> 00:31:02,690
I was swamped.

496
00:31:03,190 --> 00:31:04,400
You're always busy.

497
00:31:05,060 --> 00:31:06,130
It's already 4 p.m.

498
00:31:06,930 --> 00:31:09,970
Have you fallen out of love with me?
I won't expect a phone call.

499
00:31:10,030 --> 00:31:11,640
But you could send a text at least.

500
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,810
You're the one who acts busy.

501
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:16,270
Don't you dare turn this around on me.

502
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:20,680
- You don't eat street food, do you?
- Why wouldn't I?

503
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:24,020
It's too early for dinner,
so how about some tteokbokki? Okay?

504
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:25,920
Okay.

505
00:31:25,920 --> 00:31:27,850
Here you are. Enjoy.

506
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,290
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

507
00:31:35,430 --> 00:31:38,860
Tteokbokki was the very first thing I made
the day I moved out on my own.

508
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:41,470
I'll never forget that day.

509
00:31:42,330 --> 00:31:44,600
What was the best part
of being on your own?

510
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:50,110
Having my very own space
for the first time in my life.

511
00:31:50,580 --> 00:31:52,080
A real home, not an institution.

512
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:54,980
It was so quiet at night,
with no one snoring,

513
00:31:55,050 --> 00:31:57,480
that I couldn't sleep
because I was so happy.

514
00:31:57,550 --> 00:31:58,850
Girls snore?

515
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,790
When they're tired,
it's so loud it shakes walls.

516
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,420
You probably snore too, right?

517
00:32:02,790 --> 00:32:05,190
I don't think so.
No one's ever told me I do.

518
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:08,260
My brother says
I'm a pretty quiet sleeper for a guy.

519
00:32:10,390 --> 00:32:11,860
Have you seen my brother recently?

520
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:13,830
No.

521
00:32:15,300 --> 00:32:16,470
Listen, just in case...

522
00:32:18,300 --> 00:32:19,300
What?

523
00:32:20,070 --> 00:32:23,210
Now that my brother is getting older,
he can sometimes go overboard.

524
00:32:23,470 --> 00:32:25,740
If he does, try to be understanding.
He's my brother, after all.

525
00:32:26,410 --> 00:32:27,680
Go overboard how?

526
00:32:28,150 --> 00:32:30,720
He's just different from me in some ways.

527
00:32:42,490 --> 00:32:46,130
Sir. I just got a call
that Lee Eun Hye came to the office today.

528
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:48,400
A man claiming to be
Kim Jin Ju's father came...

529
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:49,800
and is demanding her address.

530
00:32:49,870 --> 00:32:51,470
He says he hasn't been able to reach her
for ten days.

531
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:53,840
What are you talking about? What father?

532
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:55,370
That's what I mean.

533
00:32:55,810 --> 00:32:56,940
Tell him she quit.

534
00:32:57,010 --> 00:32:58,780
We did, but he still demands her address.

535
00:32:59,110 --> 00:33:00,950
He says he knows she's in Hyeonmi-dong.

536
00:33:02,010 --> 00:33:05,650
What should I do?
He's not leaving until we give it to him.

537
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:07,690
Tell Eun Hye to call me.

538
00:33:12,390 --> 00:33:15,860
Hello.
I'm Kim Gwang Cheol, Jin Ju's father.

539
00:33:16,390 --> 00:33:17,400
I see.

540
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:19,100
Are you the CEO?

541
00:33:19,700 --> 00:33:20,900
I am. What is this about?

542
00:33:22,670 --> 00:33:26,370
On the 14th, I met my daughter, Jin Ju,
at the Joongang Hotel.

543
00:33:27,140 --> 00:33:28,210
Did you hear about that?

544
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:29,870
No.

545
00:33:30,170 --> 00:33:33,080
We even ate at the hotel's Japanese spot
before parting ways.

546
00:33:33,410 --> 00:33:35,810
But four days later, I couldn't reach her.

547
00:33:36,150 --> 00:33:37,950
Her phone's been off ever since.

548
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:40,550
She quit almost a week ago.

549
00:33:40,820 --> 00:33:42,890
Did she say she found another job?

550
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:46,160
I asked, but she said
she just wanted to take a break.

551
00:33:46,460 --> 00:33:48,630
If she'd gotten another job,
I would've heard about it right away.

552
00:33:48,690 --> 00:33:50,190
I have to go find her.

553
00:33:50,530 --> 00:33:53,300
If you don't trust me, send someone along.

554
00:33:54,070 --> 00:33:56,370
I only know that she lives
in Hyeonmi-dong.

555
00:33:57,270 --> 00:33:59,040
Please give me her address.

556
00:34:01,340 --> 00:34:03,370
You never know,
something could've happened to her.

557
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:05,210
She might have gone on a trip...

558
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:07,480
Will you take responsibility
if something happened?

559
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:11,480
Let me speak to my employee.

560
00:34:15,950 --> 00:34:16,950
Hello?

561
00:34:17,490 --> 00:34:19,890
- Yes?
- Are any of the men working today?

562
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:21,090
Hwang Jae Young.

563
00:34:22,890 --> 00:34:24,560
You didn't eat on purpose, did you?

564
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:26,860
Not at all. I really enjoyed it.

565
00:34:27,160 --> 00:34:28,700
I've been craving
the tteokbokki from here.

566
00:34:28,700 --> 00:34:29,700
(CEO James Ha)

567
00:34:30,900 --> 00:34:32,400
- It's Mr. Ha.
- I'll get it.

568
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:36,940
What's up? I'm here with Ba Ra.

569
00:34:37,010 --> 00:34:38,210
Good. Put her on.

570
00:34:38,580 --> 00:34:40,710
- Why?
- I need to ask her something.

571
00:34:40,710 --> 00:34:43,550
A man came by
claiming to be Kim Jin Ju's birth father.

572
00:34:45,350 --> 00:34:46,880
Did Kim Jin Ju meet her birth father?

573
00:34:49,220 --> 00:34:51,220
- Hello?
- It's James.

574
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:55,090
- Hello, sir.
- Please, drop the "sir."

575
00:34:55,890 --> 00:34:58,860
Did you happen to hear that
Kim Jin Ju met her birth father?

576
00:35:01,430 --> 00:35:04,500
- Yes.
- And you haven't spoken to her recently?

577
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:07,610
No, it's been a while.

578
00:35:08,170 --> 00:35:09,740
What about quitting her job with us?

579
00:35:10,510 --> 00:35:11,840
She quit?

580
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:15,450
The phone is turned off.

581
00:35:15,510 --> 00:35:18,420
Please leave a message after the tone.

582
00:35:18,420 --> 00:35:19,780
Charges will apply...

583
00:35:24,990 --> 00:35:26,720
What was the man
who claimed to be her father like?

584
00:35:27,260 --> 00:35:30,190
He was pretty well-dressed.

585
00:35:31,100 --> 00:35:32,300
What does he do for a living?

586
00:35:32,860 --> 00:35:34,100
I didn't get into that.

587
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:36,400
He said right away that I wasn't her.

588
00:35:37,270 --> 00:35:39,640
At least she met her biological father,
right?

589
00:35:41,710 --> 00:35:43,170
We're making one stop first.

590
00:35:44,380 --> 00:35:45,380
Where?

591
00:35:47,910 --> 00:35:49,750
Can't you tell me? I'm curious.

592
00:35:50,450 --> 00:35:51,480
A pet shop.

593
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,420
- I can't get a pet.
- Yes, you can.

594
00:35:54,420 --> 00:35:55,650
I can't just leave it at home alone.

595
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:57,020
I've already thought about all that.

596
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:12,070
Then, instead of buying one,
let's go to an animal shelter.

597
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:16,770
If I were in a position to have one,
I was thinking of adopting a rescue.

598
00:36:16,970 --> 00:36:18,010
Okay?

599
00:36:18,110 --> 00:36:20,240
Think it through so you have no regrets.

600
00:36:20,340 --> 00:36:22,510
I won't. I've even volunteered there.

601
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:25,880
Yong Joong.

602
00:36:27,180 --> 00:36:28,190
The address.

603
00:37:17,100 --> 00:37:21,440
I don't know who'll be the first
to read this,

604
00:37:21,740 --> 00:37:23,240
but by that time, I'll probably be...

605
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:31,850
with the grandmother I never got to meet.

606
00:37:32,120 --> 00:37:33,750
I'm so exhausted,

607
00:37:34,490 --> 00:37:36,850
and my last glimmer of hope is gone.

608
00:37:37,450 --> 00:37:39,960
I wonder what my real parents are like.

609
00:37:41,060 --> 00:37:43,590
I would dream and imagine,

610
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:46,160
and that's what gave me hope.

611
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:49,130
That's how I kept going.

612
00:37:49,730 --> 00:37:51,540
But that hope was shattered.

613
00:37:52,640 --> 00:37:54,210
Mr. James,

614
00:37:55,040 --> 00:37:58,840
I'm sorry, and thank you for everything
you've done for me.

615
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:02,950
Momo, while we worked together,

616
00:38:03,450 --> 00:38:07,150
I had so much fun
and really developed an eye for things.

617
00:38:07,690 --> 00:38:08,720
Thank you.

618
00:38:09,290 --> 00:38:10,790
We have to report this to the police,
right?

619
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:14,660
Oh my gosh!

620
00:38:15,790 --> 00:38:18,230
What is going on now? Seriously.

621
00:38:29,510 --> 00:38:31,640
I like big dogs,

622
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:33,140
but in an apartment...

623
00:38:33,280 --> 00:38:34,450
Don't worry about it.

624
00:38:34,910 --> 00:38:35,980
Choose from one of these.

625
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:38,720
(James)

626
00:38:53,660 --> 00:38:55,000
Is Reporter Geum with you?

627
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:57,800
No, it was loud,
so I stepped out to take the call.

628
00:38:57,870 --> 00:39:01,610
Kim Jin Ju, Ba Ra's orphanage friend,
disappeared, possibly to take her life.

629
00:39:03,740 --> 00:39:04,740
Are you serious?

630
00:39:05,040 --> 00:39:06,140
Yes.

631
00:39:07,110 --> 00:39:09,250
- Why?
- I don't know the details,

632
00:39:09,250 --> 00:39:11,850
but Reporter Geum
is going to be devastated. This is awful.

633
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:15,490
What do we do?
I heard they grew up like sisters.

634
00:39:15,850 --> 00:39:16,850
Are you sure about this?

635
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:18,920
Her father and a staff member of mine
went to her home,

636
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:20,660
and they found a letter she'd left behind.

637
00:39:46,250 --> 00:39:47,790
Just when I finally met her.

638
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:51,820
After everything I went through
to find her.

639
00:40:02,270 --> 00:40:03,330
Ba Ra.

640
00:40:04,130 --> 00:40:06,200
Even if I didn't always show it,

641
00:40:06,870 --> 00:40:09,210
and if there were ever times I hurt you,

642
00:40:10,410 --> 00:40:12,510
because we were like sisters,

643
00:40:13,510 --> 00:40:15,110
please just remember the good times.

644
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:20,050
Having you with me
really made it less lonely.

645
00:40:20,650 --> 00:40:21,920
You were such a big support for me.

646
00:40:23,750 --> 00:40:28,690
When I think about it,
I must have been happiest in the womb.

647
00:40:29,330 --> 00:40:30,890
They say even fetuses can feel things,
you know.

648
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,130
You know I've always loved water, right?

649
00:40:34,700 --> 00:40:37,630
I'm going to find my peace in the water.

650
00:40:39,070 --> 00:40:41,740
I thought we would be
like a family forever.

651
00:40:43,710 --> 00:40:45,280
A wave of sadness is washing over me.

652
00:41:03,690 --> 00:41:05,030
Jin Ju, eat up.

653
00:41:05,460 --> 00:41:07,700
- I heard your grades went up.
- Yes, they did.

654
00:41:08,970 --> 00:41:10,100
Eat up.

655
00:41:12,770 --> 00:41:14,100
Eat up.

656
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:20,880
Hey, did you get a banana?

657
00:41:21,450 --> 00:41:22,450
Yes.

658
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:28,890
If you get adopted,
that lady won't volunteer anymore, right?

659
00:41:28,950 --> 00:41:31,760
She said she'd keep coming.
She finds it rewarding.

660
00:41:31,820 --> 00:41:33,420
Will you come back and visit?

661
00:41:34,260 --> 00:41:37,130
- I'm going to miss you.
- Me too.

662
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,860
I can't come weekly because of school,
but I'll visit as often as I can.

663
00:41:43,270 --> 00:41:47,240
Everything should be finalized
by next week.

664
00:41:47,700 --> 00:41:48,770
Thank you.

665
00:41:49,070 --> 00:41:50,670
You've worked so hard for us.

666
00:41:50,870 --> 00:41:53,810
To be honest, our foundation's chairman...

667
00:41:53,940 --> 00:41:56,550
really doted on Ba Ra
and thinks the world of her.

668
00:41:56,550 --> 00:41:58,420
It's not that he was against it,

669
00:41:58,750 --> 00:42:00,250
but he wasn't exactly thrilled about it.

670
00:42:00,950 --> 00:42:04,460
He kept asking why it had to be her,
saying she's the face of the orphanage.

671
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:06,920
It's impossible not to love Ba Ra.

672
00:42:07,060 --> 00:42:09,130
She's so kind and hardworking.

673
00:42:10,130 --> 00:42:11,130
Excuse me.

674
00:42:14,400 --> 00:42:15,430
What?

675
00:42:15,630 --> 00:42:17,400
Did you lose something?

676
00:42:18,270 --> 00:42:21,000
- My wallet...
- Your wallet is missing?

677
00:42:22,340 --> 00:42:25,510
Hello? Hi, honey.
I'll call you right back.

678
00:42:28,110 --> 00:42:29,380
Everyone, down to the auditorium.

679
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:31,780
Deok Young, go and get
Mi Su and Seon Uk. Quickly.

680
00:42:31,850 --> 00:42:32,850
Okay.

681
00:42:46,430 --> 00:42:48,470
Don't just glance around.
Search everywhere!

682
00:42:48,970 --> 00:42:50,000
We have to find it.

683
00:42:53,600 --> 00:42:54,610
(Kim Jin Ju)

684
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:02,050
Is this...

685
00:43:02,450 --> 00:43:03,450
Thank you.

686
00:43:08,290 --> 00:43:10,550
Is anything missing?

687
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:14,660
There was 500 dollars in cash.

688
00:43:16,090 --> 00:43:19,130
I'm positive I put exactly 500 dollars
in here.

689
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:20,760
All in new bills...

690
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:23,270
I was going to give it to the kids
for their allowance.

691
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:25,200
(Geum Ba Ra)

692
00:43:48,060 --> 00:43:49,530
Why would I do that?

693
00:43:50,460 --> 00:43:52,360
I have no reason to.

694
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:00,400
Go to your room.

695
00:44:02,170 --> 00:44:03,170
Didn't you hear me?

696
00:44:17,750 --> 00:44:20,390
(Unpo Police Station)

697
00:44:21,660 --> 00:44:23,830
Her phone's last signal was
at Yeongdeung Port.

698
00:44:24,330 --> 00:44:26,230
And we've seen no signs of activity since.

699
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:28,230
Considering she left a note,
it's pretty clear.

700
00:44:29,630 --> 00:44:30,630
But you can't be sure.

701
00:44:31,030 --> 00:44:32,200
She might've faked it
to escape her father.

702
00:44:32,470 --> 00:44:34,470
Then she would've at least taken money
or her credit cards.

703
00:44:35,040 --> 00:44:36,770
Her bank accounts and debit card
are untouched.

704
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:38,840
I'm telling you,
there's no sign of activity.

705
00:44:40,380 --> 00:44:43,110
- We have Kim Jin Ju on CCTV.
- Where?

706
00:44:43,110 --> 00:44:44,380
A convenience store at Yeongdeung Port.

707
00:44:53,890 --> 00:44:55,230
Does this make any sense to you, Ba Ra?

708
00:44:55,490 --> 00:44:56,930
I can't believe it either.

709
00:44:57,430 --> 00:44:58,930
Is she that fragile?

710
00:44:59,760 --> 00:45:02,570
- She must be somewhere...
- This might be out of line,

711
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:04,400
but have you considered that...

712
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,440
she might not be your biological daughter,
although the facts might line up?

713
00:45:14,440 --> 00:45:16,280
I already had it checked, just in case.

714
00:45:16,650 --> 00:45:18,750
I got a hold of her toothbrush
and some hair.

715
00:45:22,690 --> 00:45:25,660
(DNA analysis report)

716
00:45:27,860 --> 00:45:29,660
(Test result details)

717
00:45:29,730 --> 00:45:32,200
(Genetic match test results:
99.99 percent paternity match verified)

718
00:45:32,260 --> 00:45:34,970
(Paternity between Kim Gwang Cheol
and Kim Jin Ju is confirmed)

719
00:45:36,970 --> 00:45:41,370
I didn't even know she existed,
and this is how she twists the knife?

720
00:45:42,840 --> 00:45:44,410
I need Momo's number.

721
00:45:45,140 --> 00:45:47,840
Someone like Momo
could easily be hiding her.

722
00:45:49,850 --> 00:45:52,050
Momo just had a death in her family, too.

723
00:45:52,450 --> 00:45:54,380
She has neither the time
nor the reason to do that.

724
00:45:55,620 --> 00:45:57,090
What are you, her spokesperson?

725
00:45:58,920 --> 00:45:59,920
Whatever.

726
00:46:01,760 --> 00:46:04,230
- I only have her agency's number.
- And you're a reporter?

727
00:46:04,630 --> 00:46:07,460
You have no idea how strict
celebrity agencies are in Korea.

728
00:46:09,770 --> 00:46:11,400
Especially with reporters.

729
00:46:12,340 --> 00:46:14,370
No matter what her biological father
was like,

730
00:46:14,940 --> 00:46:18,610
how could she just throw her life away?
That has to be the only reason.

731
00:46:18,740 --> 00:46:20,140
She must have been
incredibly disappointed.

732
00:46:20,910 --> 00:46:22,310
Especially since she saw
the ankle bracelet.

733
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:24,750
I'd be horrified too, if I were her.

734
00:46:25,520 --> 00:46:27,250
Especially with some man
who's claiming to be your father.

735
00:46:28,520 --> 00:46:30,320
- Manager Yoon.
- Yes?

736
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:34,290
Let's live a long, full life.
No matter what hardships we face.

737
00:46:34,790 --> 00:46:35,790
Right.

738
00:46:39,130 --> 00:46:40,130
You don't think...

739
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:44,670
Do you think she might have
gone to Momo's?

740
00:46:45,340 --> 00:46:48,340
- No way.
- But Jin Ju was so good to Momo.

741
00:46:48,870 --> 00:46:51,210
Even though Jin Ju's the older one,
she catered to her every whim.

742
00:46:51,940 --> 00:46:54,040
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

743
00:46:55,050 --> 00:46:56,150
You haven't heard from her, have you?

744
00:46:57,210 --> 00:46:58,850
I haven't spoken to her in ages.

745
00:47:00,320 --> 00:47:01,320
Okay, got it.

746
00:47:02,950 --> 00:47:04,220
Are you going to stay there?

747
00:47:04,490 --> 00:47:06,860
I hurt my back a little.
It's a long story.

748
00:47:07,490 --> 00:47:09,160
Besides, she probably just
went off the grid for a bit.

749
00:47:09,460 --> 00:47:12,000
It's absurd to think she'd kill herself
over something like that.

750
00:47:13,630 --> 00:47:16,130
- That's a relief.
- On the 23rd, it's Director Shin's...

751
00:47:16,870 --> 00:47:19,670
It's his birthday. Come with CEO Ha.

752
00:47:20,370 --> 00:47:22,740
Why would I go? He can go by himself.

753
00:47:22,740 --> 00:47:24,540
You two came here together late.

754
00:47:25,840 --> 00:47:27,280
Only because he asked me to come.

755
00:47:27,710 --> 00:47:28,710
I'm getting a call.

756
00:47:29,450 --> 00:47:30,450
Yes.

757
00:47:32,350 --> 00:47:33,980
If she dies, it's her own loss.

758
00:47:36,820 --> 00:47:39,720
Anything's better than being dead.

759
00:49:46,380 --> 00:49:48,720
(Surgery time, Current time,
Anesthesia time)

760
00:50:06,400 --> 00:50:08,940
Ever tried Baijiu? It's a Chinese liquor.

761
00:50:10,270 --> 00:50:11,270
No, I haven't.

762
00:50:19,050 --> 00:50:20,320
Don't bother sipping it.

763
00:50:21,250 --> 00:50:22,250
Just throw it back in one go.

764
00:50:31,390 --> 00:50:33,960
It might seem strong,
but you won't have a hangover tomorrow.

765
00:50:34,630 --> 00:50:35,630
Okay.

766
00:50:48,680 --> 00:50:49,910
Are you happy with your life?

767
00:50:51,450 --> 00:50:53,780
I'm just trying to do my best.

768
00:50:55,250 --> 00:50:56,250
I'm asking if you're happy.

769
00:50:58,320 --> 00:50:59,960
You want me to be honest?

770
00:51:00,620 --> 00:51:01,660
You should be,

771
00:51:02,630 --> 00:51:03,630
especially with a good drink like this.

772
00:51:08,300 --> 00:51:09,300
I'm struggling.

773
00:51:26,220 --> 00:51:27,220
Kim Jin Ju.

774
00:51:29,350 --> 00:51:30,350
Yes?

775
00:51:31,250 --> 00:51:32,620
Ever think about getting on
an operating table?

776
00:51:34,590 --> 00:51:37,060
If you do, I can change your life.

777
00:51:39,260 --> 00:51:41,730
Director Shin, you do plastic surgery too?

778
00:51:43,670 --> 00:51:44,770
A surgery to reshape your life.

779
00:51:46,970 --> 00:51:47,970
It's possible.

780
00:51:54,180 --> 00:51:55,610
Don't you want to live like Momo?

781
00:51:56,980 --> 00:51:57,980
As Momo.

782
00:52:00,020 --> 00:52:01,020
I'm not kidding.

783
00:52:03,890 --> 00:52:05,490
I'm going to be honest with you tonight.

784
00:52:06,890 --> 00:52:07,960
So you have to keep this a secret.

785
00:52:14,500 --> 00:52:15,500
Take it to your grave.

786
00:52:18,970 --> 00:52:19,970
Yes.

787
00:52:24,740 --> 00:52:27,110
The Momo you see now is
only Momo on the outside.

788
00:52:30,980 --> 00:52:33,880
After the accident, she was a complete...

789
00:52:40,220 --> 00:52:41,220
a complete wreck.

790
00:52:44,030 --> 00:52:45,430
How could her mother bear to see...

791
00:52:46,160 --> 00:52:47,360
her own daughter in such a state?

792
00:52:48,700 --> 00:52:50,900
And this is the world-famous Momo
we're talking about.

793
00:52:52,400 --> 00:52:53,400
So I...

794
00:52:55,140 --> 00:52:56,740
Momo's mother was the one
who suggested it,

795
00:52:57,970 --> 00:52:59,310
but regardless, I did the surgery.

796
00:53:05,280 --> 00:53:06,280
It was a success.

797
00:53:10,150 --> 00:53:11,150
But...

798
00:53:12,390 --> 00:53:13,820
people can have a change of heart.

799
00:53:14,990 --> 00:53:18,160
The plan was for me to break up with her
naturally after the brain swap,

800
00:53:21,970 --> 00:53:23,170
but now she has other ideas.

801
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:28,070
No matter how much she looks
like Momo on the outside,

802
00:53:31,040 --> 00:53:32,040
on the inside,

803
00:53:36,410 --> 00:53:37,580
it's my future mother-in-law.

804
00:53:39,880 --> 00:53:40,880
How could that possibly work...

805
00:53:42,490 --> 00:53:43,550
from my perspective?

806
00:53:48,160 --> 00:53:49,430
I can't even imagine.

807
00:53:54,360 --> 00:53:55,370
Jin Ju.

808
00:53:57,470 --> 00:53:58,540
I'm not forcing you.

809
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:02,770
But I want it to be you.

810
00:54:10,880 --> 00:54:12,980
Is that really possible?

811
00:54:16,250 --> 00:54:18,820
If you don't believe me,
go meet Momo and ask her some questions.

812
00:54:19,190 --> 00:54:20,290
Ask her about her old job.

813
00:54:20,990 --> 00:54:24,460
Or you could just casually part her hair
and check for the surgery scar.

814
00:54:30,130 --> 00:54:31,300
What do you think of me?

815
00:54:32,400 --> 00:54:35,040
Not as the Chairman of the orphanage
or the hospital director,

816
00:54:35,610 --> 00:54:37,440
but just as Shin Ju Shin, the man.

817
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:40,710
Aren't you interested in finding out?

818
00:54:45,250 --> 00:54:47,620
I couldn't possibly...

819
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:52,820
Strip away the titles,
and we're all just people.

820
00:54:53,360 --> 00:54:55,060
Just a man and a woman.

821
00:54:57,030 --> 00:54:58,090
For a while now,

822
00:54:59,860 --> 00:55:02,700
I feel like you've been slowly
finding a place in my heart.

823
00:55:03,770 --> 00:55:04,770
We're similar in a way.

824
00:55:05,670 --> 00:55:06,670
You're an orphan too.

825
00:55:07,700 --> 00:55:08,970
Now that all my family is gone...

826
00:55:12,680 --> 00:55:13,840
And with what's happened to Momo...

827
00:55:16,850 --> 00:55:17,850
I'm lonely.

828
00:55:20,380 --> 00:55:21,780
But what if it fails?

829
00:55:23,220 --> 00:55:24,420
What would happen to me then?

830
00:55:27,220 --> 00:55:28,560
I'm fine out here.

831
00:55:32,100 --> 00:55:35,200
I'm starving. You got anything to eat?
Even just some ramyeon?

832
00:55:38,640 --> 00:55:39,800
We can't afford any mistakes.

833
00:55:40,570 --> 00:55:44,340
You'll become Momo, have and enjoy
everything you've ever wanted,

834
00:55:46,080 --> 00:55:47,510
including all of her wealth,
automatically.

835
00:55:50,210 --> 00:55:53,150
So then, CEO Hyun Ran Hee
would take my body?

836
00:55:55,120 --> 00:55:58,150
If CEO Hyun's brain
were to go into your body,

837
00:55:59,420 --> 00:56:02,130
do you think she'd just accept that
and live quietly?

838
00:56:08,500 --> 00:56:09,500
Actually...

839
00:56:12,170 --> 00:56:13,170
Go on.

840
00:56:16,010 --> 00:56:18,340
A man claiming to be
my biological father showed up.

841
00:56:20,680 --> 00:56:21,680
Really?

842
00:56:38,230 --> 00:56:39,630
That smug Geum Ba Ra...

843
00:56:40,930 --> 00:56:42,770
Just you watch
what this Kim Jin Ju becomes.

844
00:56:50,010 --> 00:56:51,110
I...

845
00:56:52,210 --> 00:56:53,980
I, Kim Jin Ju...

846
00:56:54,940 --> 00:56:55,950
will become Momo.

847
00:57:05,860 --> 00:57:07,160
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

848
00:57:12,460 --> 00:57:14,700
- Hello?
- It's me.

849
00:57:16,500 --> 00:57:18,500
- Yes.
- Are you done with work?

850
00:57:19,640 --> 00:57:20,700
I'm at a work dinner.

851
00:57:21,440 --> 00:57:22,910
Then why's it so quiet?

852
00:57:23,340 --> 00:57:24,370
I'm in the bathroom.

853
00:57:25,070 --> 00:57:26,080
Okay.

854
00:57:27,110 --> 00:57:30,080
I'd like to buy you an outfit tomorrow.
Are you free?

855
00:57:31,910 --> 00:57:34,520
I feel bad that I haven't done
anything for you.

856
00:57:38,450 --> 00:57:39,790
I have a shoot that runs late.

857
00:57:42,530 --> 00:57:43,530
What about Sunday, then?

858
00:57:46,200 --> 00:57:47,230
I'll give you a call.

859
00:57:48,970 --> 00:57:50,130
We're not strangers anymore.

860
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:52,070
You can stop being so formal.

861
00:57:54,570 --> 00:57:55,570
Okay.

862
00:57:55,640 --> 00:57:56,640
All right.

863
00:59:14,780 --> 00:59:15,990
Kim Jin Ju.

864
00:59:17,150 --> 00:59:18,790
You've lived such a sad life.

865
00:59:51,890 --> 00:59:54,360
(Power off)

866
00:59:56,890 --> 00:59:58,460
(Power off)

867
01:02:16,370 --> 01:02:17,430
Jin Ju, have a seat.

868
01:02:22,140 --> 01:02:24,970
- Does Reporter Geum like dogs?
- I think so.

869
01:02:25,340 --> 01:02:27,340
She always stops to look at dogs
when we pass them.

870
01:02:27,540 --> 01:02:29,650
What kind does she like? Small breeds?

871
01:02:30,250 --> 01:02:31,450
Or a bigger dog, like a poodle?

872
01:02:31,780 --> 01:02:32,780
Should I ask her?

873
01:02:33,250 --> 01:02:35,650
No. She even returned the painting,

874
01:02:35,720 --> 01:02:37,790
so I thought she might accept
a living gift.

875
01:02:40,620 --> 01:02:41,620
Sir.

876
01:02:42,590 --> 01:02:43,960
I'd like to take some time off.

877
01:02:45,130 --> 01:02:46,130
For how long?

878
01:02:47,460 --> 01:02:48,460
About a year.

879
01:02:49,200 --> 01:02:50,370
And that was it.

880
01:02:52,740 --> 01:02:54,240
And she got her severance pay?

881
01:02:54,300 --> 01:02:55,710
Of course.

882
01:02:57,770 --> 01:03:00,710
Did she mention meeting me?

883
01:03:01,210 --> 01:03:02,210
Not a single word.

884
01:03:02,750 --> 01:03:04,680
When she was working as Momo's stylist,

885
01:03:05,010 --> 01:03:06,380
how did the two of them get along?

886
01:03:06,720 --> 01:03:07,980
They were very close.

887
01:03:14,890 --> 01:03:15,890
Hey, Yong Joong.

888
01:03:16,260 --> 01:03:17,860
You have something tonight, don't you?

889
01:03:18,730 --> 01:03:20,700
What's with your voice? Are you sick?

890
01:03:21,230 --> 01:03:22,300
A little.

891
01:03:22,630 --> 01:03:24,000
What's wrong? Did you take anything?

892
01:03:24,130 --> 01:03:27,600
I don't really take medicine.
Why don't you come make me some porridge?

893
01:03:27,700 --> 01:03:28,870
Is the housekeeper not there?

894
01:03:29,410 --> 01:03:31,770
She's a terrible cook
when it comes to porridge.

895
01:03:44,420 --> 01:03:46,820
The passcode is the last four digits
of my phone number.

896
01:04:09,880 --> 01:04:10,950
Hey...

897
01:04:11,350 --> 01:04:12,350
Here.

898
01:04:18,050 --> 01:04:19,050
He's the one, right?

899
01:04:19,320 --> 01:04:20,320
Are you feeling better already?

900
01:04:20,990 --> 01:04:21,990
Give him a name.

901
01:04:23,260 --> 01:04:24,660
You scared me.

902
01:04:25,360 --> 01:04:27,930
I already gave him a bath,
and he's had all his shots.

903
01:04:28,200 --> 01:04:30,270
I didn't know you could pull off
a surprise like this.

904
01:04:30,670 --> 01:04:32,640
It's a birthday present
to make up for all the ones I missed.

905
01:04:37,940 --> 01:04:39,740
But I'm the only one getting gifts.

906
01:04:39,740 --> 01:04:40,810
That's what older brothers are for.

907
01:04:41,610 --> 01:04:44,310
Drop by to see him anytime.
Better yet, just move in.

908
01:04:46,380 --> 01:04:49,020
It's sweet of you to say that. Thank you.

909
01:04:49,320 --> 01:04:50,950
I mean it.

910
01:04:51,720 --> 01:04:53,220
I want to do something for you too.

911
01:04:55,260 --> 01:04:56,260
There is one thing.

912
01:04:59,430 --> 01:05:01,330
Put my mind at ease.

913
01:05:04,400 --> 01:05:06,170
I haven't done anything to worry you.

914
01:05:06,970 --> 01:05:08,640
I'll never cause you any trouble.

915
01:05:09,670 --> 01:05:11,010
Because I don't want anything from you.

916
01:05:13,280 --> 01:05:14,280
What's that supposed to mean?

917
01:05:15,310 --> 01:05:16,310
Exactly what it sounds like.

918
01:05:17,380 --> 01:05:19,450
Go on, ask for things. I can afford it.

919
01:05:20,150 --> 01:05:21,150
Just...

920
01:05:23,020 --> 01:05:24,590
having you is enough for me.

921
01:05:25,150 --> 01:05:28,420
It's incredible that I get to see you.
It's been almost 20 years.

922
01:05:32,460 --> 01:05:35,830
When I was in elementary school,
the one thing I begged my mom for...

923
01:05:36,700 --> 01:05:38,870
was a little sister.

924
01:05:39,440 --> 01:05:42,000
But she'd just give me a vague smile
and brush me off.

925
01:05:42,640 --> 01:05:44,270
Looking back on it now,

926
01:05:44,770 --> 01:05:48,510
my mom was over 40.
I guess she didn't think she could do it.

927
01:05:48,940 --> 01:05:51,310
If she'd explained it better,
I would've gotten it.

928
01:05:52,750 --> 01:05:55,450
She underestimated her son's maturity.

929
01:05:56,620 --> 01:05:58,720
So how could I not be completely smitten
with my little one?

930
01:05:59,120 --> 01:06:00,120
At first sight?

931
01:06:02,290 --> 01:06:03,830
I'm about to turn 30.

932
01:06:04,160 --> 01:06:05,430
Don't I age too?

933
01:06:06,530 --> 01:06:07,530
To me,

934
01:06:08,700 --> 01:06:10,630
you'll always be that little kid
from the corner store.

935
01:06:21,880 --> 01:06:25,280
In a past life, we must've been
brother and sister,

936
01:06:25,650 --> 01:06:27,280
or maybe a father and daughter?

937
01:06:27,950 --> 01:06:29,020
You believe in past lives?

938
01:06:29,790 --> 01:06:31,720
Logically, it makes sense that they do.

939
01:06:34,960 --> 01:06:36,960
I guess I must've committed a lot of sins
in my past life.

940
01:06:37,360 --> 01:06:39,700
People would swear at you for saying that.

941
01:06:39,760 --> 01:06:40,900
They'd ask if you've looked in a mirror.

942
01:06:44,030 --> 01:06:45,370
Focus on what you have.

943
01:06:48,170 --> 01:06:49,170
You've got me.

944
01:06:50,470 --> 01:06:52,440
You're my everything.

945
01:06:54,140 --> 01:06:55,210
But don't feel pressured.

946
01:06:55,910 --> 01:06:57,710
Pressured? We confessed
our feelings to each other.

947
01:07:00,720 --> 01:07:03,150
The housekeeper left a whole feast for us.

948
01:07:19,600 --> 01:07:20,940
It's not your birthday, though.

949
01:07:21,240 --> 01:07:22,470
It's your belated birthday dinner.

950
01:07:25,070 --> 01:07:27,910
You've already had plenty to eat.
All you can do is watch.

951
01:07:29,140 --> 01:07:31,080
I told her to make it
a kid's birthday meal.

952
01:07:33,150 --> 01:07:35,580
You're not wired like other guys.

953
01:07:36,420 --> 01:07:38,890
Is that a compliment?
Are you saying I'm androgynous?

954
01:07:40,320 --> 01:07:43,030
It means you were raised right.

955
01:07:43,730 --> 01:07:46,030
You're considerate and thoughtful.

956
01:07:46,460 --> 01:07:47,960
I was raised right,

957
01:07:48,400 --> 01:07:50,270
but I went through a serious angsty phase
as a freshman.

958
01:07:51,470 --> 01:07:53,170
Do you look just like your dad?

959
01:07:53,170 --> 01:07:55,040
Not at all.
I'll show you a photo after we eat.

960
01:07:56,370 --> 01:07:58,510
- I should heat up the soup.
- It's okay. I don't like it too hot.

961
01:07:58,770 --> 01:08:00,440
Seaweed soup is fine
when it's not super hot.

962
01:08:07,180 --> 01:08:08,180
Hey...

963
01:08:09,490 --> 01:08:11,590
I don't want to lose you
to some other woman.

964
01:08:12,350 --> 01:08:13,360
You're too good for them.

965
01:08:13,660 --> 01:08:14,890
Then just keep me by your side forever.

966
01:08:15,160 --> 01:08:16,230
I'm serious.

967
01:08:17,990 --> 01:08:18,990
Even if I get married,

968
01:08:19,530 --> 01:08:21,530
how I feel about my kiddo
will never change.

969
01:08:22,700 --> 01:08:24,970
Does he not see me as a woman at all?

970
01:08:35,040 --> 01:08:36,580
Your housekeeper is an amazing cook.

971
01:08:37,650 --> 01:08:39,950
I specifically asked for marinated beef
instead of the braised ribs.

972
01:08:40,920 --> 01:08:43,890
Because when I was a kid,
I thought marinated beef was tastier.

973
01:08:44,250 --> 01:08:45,390
And now you prefer the ribs?

974
01:08:45,690 --> 01:08:46,690
Steak.

975
01:08:47,890 --> 01:08:48,890
Royal court rice cakes.

976
01:08:51,490 --> 01:08:53,700
- Are these rice or wheat cakes?
- Rice cakes.

977
01:08:53,800 --> 01:08:55,130
I like the rice cakes, too.

978
01:09:04,310 --> 01:09:05,340
Ever since I met you again,

979
01:09:06,840 --> 01:09:08,080
I've been so happy.

980
01:09:16,320 --> 01:09:17,320
I'm the one who should be saying that.

981
01:09:19,220 --> 01:09:20,260
What are you going to name him?

982
01:09:25,430 --> 01:09:26,430
Pickles.

983
01:09:30,270 --> 01:09:33,270
Have you heard from Director Shin?
About a birthday invite.

984
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:35,000
No.

985
01:09:35,740 --> 01:09:37,140
Momo said she was going to invite you.

986
01:09:38,510 --> 01:09:39,810
Ju Shin hates that stuff.

987
01:09:40,740 --> 01:09:42,950
He hasn't celebrated his birthday
since his mother passed away.

988
01:09:45,480 --> 01:09:49,420
Before his mother passed away,
what was Director Shin like?

989
01:09:49,690 --> 01:09:50,850
Do people ever really change?

990
01:09:51,120 --> 01:09:54,190
Even back then, was he blunt?
If that's a nice way of putting it.

991
01:09:54,960 --> 01:09:56,020
What would be a bad way of putting it?

992
01:09:56,960 --> 01:09:58,260
There's nothing bad, really.

993
01:09:58,360 --> 01:10:01,330
He may not be warm,
but he's not one to look down on people.

994
01:11:32,790 --> 01:11:35,560
(Doctor Shin)

995
01:11:35,790 --> 01:11:37,660
You're with some other guy right now.

996
01:11:38,860 --> 01:11:40,260
You must be here to run
an errand for my guy.

997
01:11:40,260 --> 01:11:41,330
Here to pick something up?

998
01:11:41,430 --> 01:11:43,430
Don't you ever think
Geum Ba Ra is a little too smart?

999
01:11:43,670 --> 01:11:44,700
What's wrong with being smart?

1000
01:11:44,700 --> 01:11:48,100
I see Ba Ra as a sister, not a woman.

1001
01:11:48,200 --> 01:11:50,040
Do you think she feels the same way?

1002
01:11:50,140 --> 01:11:51,940
- Can you video call?
- Yes.

1003
01:11:52,640 --> 01:11:54,080
Look at me and go potty.

1004
01:11:54,080 --> 01:11:55,510
My love has begun...

1005
01:11:55,980 --> 01:11:57,350
with Director Shin Ju Shin.

1006
01:11:57,610 --> 01:11:59,350
Do you think I could get an MRI?

1007
01:11:59,350 --> 01:12:00,480
Are you feeling unwell?

1008
01:12:01,280 --> 01:12:02,880
Email me Geum Ba Ra's files.

1009
01:12:03,150 --> 01:12:05,020
- All of them.
- Understood.

1010
01:12:05,090 --> 01:12:06,360
What are your thoughts on a brain swap?

1011
01:12:06,620 --> 01:12:07,660
Have you ever thought about it?

1012
01:12:07,720 --> 01:12:10,460
You mean how they say AI can replace
an entire human brain?

1013
01:12:10,530 --> 01:12:11,530
The face would stay the same.

1014
01:12:12,630 --> 01:12:14,160
If we could swap only the brain...

1015
01:12:14,300 --> 01:12:16,300
You mean you, Director?

1016
01:12:21,800 --> 01:12:23,810
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

